    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the pottery style found in the northern Levant from about 5500 to 5000 BCE. The style is characterized by vessels covered with a red wash that are sometimes decorated with plain reserve bands with impressed or incised ornamentation.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica encontrado al norte del Levante desde aproximadamente 5500 al 5000 a.C. El estilo se caracteriza por vasos cubiertos con un lavado rojo que a veces se decora con bandas lisas con ornamentación grabada o incisa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de stijl van het in de noordelijke Levant gevonden aardwerk uit de periode van circa 5.500 tot 5.000 v. Chr. De stijl kenmerkt zich door kruiken die zijn bedekt met een rode laklaag, soms versierd met eenvoudige, ingetogen banden met ingedrukte of ingekerfde versieringen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指自西元前5500年至西元前5000年間，於黎凡特北部發展的陶器風格。其特色為覆上一層紅色塗料的陶器器皿，表面有時會以雕刻或壓印裝飾花紋的素面飾帶作為裝飾。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
